Comparison of the obtained sequences revealed a high nt identity (99.97–99.95%) between the detected strains. In the common tract of the obtained sequences (4329 nt), differences were observed at five nucleotide residues: at nt residue 716, 1189 and 1608 of the NS1 gene (Table 2
) and at nt residues 876 and 1731 of the VP2 gene (Table 3
).
